The direction vector of line $l$ is $\begin{pmatrix} 4 \\ 3 \end{pmatrix}$, and the direction vector of line $m$ is $\begin{pmatrix} 4 \\ 3 \end{pmatrix}$, so we can take $\begin{pmatrix} 4 \\ 3 \end{pmatrix}$ as our unit vector $\mathbf{u}$.

Let $A = (1 + 4t, 4 + 3t)$ and $B = (-5 + 4s, 6 + 3s)$.  Then $\overrightarrow{BA} = \begin{pmatrix} 1 + 4t - (-5 + 4s) \\ 4 + 3t - (6 + 3s) \end{pmatrix} = \begin{pmatrix} 4t + 4s + 6 \\ 3t - 3s - 2 \end{pmatrix}$.

[asy]
