Let $\mathbf{v} = \begin{pmatrix} v_1 \\ v_2 \end{pmatrix}$ be the vector onto which $\overrightarrow{BA}$ is projected.  Then
\[\mathbf{v} = \frac{\begin{pmatrix} 4t + 4s + 6 \\ 3t - 3s - 2 \end{pmatrix} \cdot \begin{pmatrix} 4 \\ 3 \end{pmatrix}}{\begin{pmatrix} 4 \\ 3 \end{pmatrix} \cdot \begin{pmatrix} 4 \\ 3 \end{pmatrix}} \begin{pmatrix} 4 \\ 3 \end{pmatrix} = \frac{25t + 25s + 18}{25} \begin{pmatrix} 4 \\ 3 \end{pmatrix}.\]Hence, $v_1 = \frac{100t + 100s + 72}{25}$ and $v_2 = \frac{75t + 75s + 54}{25}$, so $v_1 + v_2 = \boxed{\frac{54}{5}}.$

Let $A = (1 + 4t, 4 + 3t)$ and $B = (-5 + 4s, 6 + 3s).$  Then $\overrightarrow{BA} = \begin{pmatrix} 1 + 4t - (-5 + 4s) \\ 4 + 3t - (6 + 3s) \end{pmatrix} = \begin{pmatrix} 4s - 4t - 6 \\ 3s - 3t - 2 \end{pmatrix}.$

[asy]
