Let $\begin{pmatrix} v_1 \\ v_2 \end{pmatrix}$ be the vector onto which $\overrightarrow{BA}$ is projected.  Then
\[\begin{pmatrix} 4s - 4t - 6 \\ 3s - 3t - 2 \end{pmatrix} = k \begin{pmatrix} v_1 \\ v_2 \end{pmatrix}\]for some constant $k.$  Taking the dot product with $\begin{pmatrix} 1 \\ 1 \end{pmatrix},$ we get
\[(4s - 4t - 6) + (3s - 3t - 2) = 2kv_1 + 2kv_2 = 4k.\]Hence, $k = \frac{4s - 4t - 6 + 3s - 3t - 2}{4} = s - t - \frac{4}{3}.$  Then
\[\begin{pmatrix} v_1 \\ v_2 \end{pmatrix} = \frac{1}{4k} \begin{pmatrix} 4s - 4t - 6 \\ 3s - 3t - 2 \end{pmatrix} = \boxed{\begin{pmatrix} \frac{s - t - 3/2}{s - t - 4/3} \\ \frac{s - t - 1}{s - t - 4/3} \end{pmatrix}}.\]

The direction vector of line $l$ is $\begin{pmatrix} 4 \\ 3 \end{pmatrix}$, and the direction vector of line $m$ is $\begin{pmatrix} 4 \\ 3 \end{pmatrix}$, so the vector $\begin{pmatrix} v_1 \\ v_2 \end{pmatrix}$ must be a scalar multiple of $\begin{pmatrix} 4 \\ 3 \end{pmatrix}$. Let $\begin{pmatrix} v_1 \\ v_2 \end{pmatrix} = c \begin{pmatrix} 4 \\ 3 \end{pmatrix}$.

[asy]
unitsize(0.5 cm);

pair A, B, P;

A = (1,4);
B = (-5,6);
P = foot(A,B,B + (4,3));

draw((0,0)--(1,4),Arrow(6));
draw((0,0)--(-5,6),Arrow(6));
draw(B--P);
draw(A--P);

label("$\begin{pmatrix} 4 \\ 3 \end{pmatrix}$", (0.5,2));
label("$\begin{pmatrix} v_1 \\ v_2 \end{pmatrix}$", (1.5,5.5));
label("$A$", A, N);
label("$B$", B, N);
label("$P$", P, SE);
[/asy]

Then $\overrightarrow{PA}$ is the projection of $\overrightarrow{BA}$ onto $\begin{pmatrix} v_1 \\ v_2 \end{pmatrix}$, so
\[\frac{\begin{pmatrix} v_1 \\ v_2 \end{pmatrix} \cdot \begin{pmatrix} 4 \\ 3 \end{pmatrix}}{\begin{pmatrix} 4 \\ 3 \end{pmatrix} \cdot \begin{pmatrix} 4 \\ 3 \end{pmatrix}} \begin{pmatrix} 4 \\ 3 \end{pmatrix} = \frac{4v_1 + 3v_2}{25} \begin{pmatrix} 4 \\ 3 \end{pmatrix}.\]Since $\overrightarrow{PA}$ is a scalar multiple of $\begin{pmatrix} 4 \\ 3 \end{pmatrix}$, the coefficient of $\begin{pmatrix} 4 \\ 3 \end{pmatrix}$ must be 1.  Hence,
\[\frac{4v_1 + 3v_2}{25} = 1.\]Since $v_1 + v_2 = 2,$ $v_2 = 2 - v_1.$  Then
\[\frac{4v_1 + 3(2 - v_1)}{25} = 1.\]Solving for $v_1$, we find $v_1 = \boxed{\frac{7}{5}}.$

